Job.Name: Brandjectory - Platform Manager
Job.Description:
Rate: 70-90 - lets estimate this based on a range Hours: 20 hours / week
Platform Manager Role Description The Brandjectory Platform Manager will be the everyday driver of the online platform’s performance and user experience, ensuring that all functionality is operational and accessible to users, all messaging is current and appropriate and any user issues or queries are resolved within a reasonable time period. The Platform Manager will combine a suite of relevant SaaS and digital marketing skills with strong business acumen and interpersonal skills to ensure every user sees the best side of the Brandjectory platform and feels like a part of a coherent, food and beverage-specific, community. Specific responsibilities of the Platform Manager will include: • Keeping all sections of the platform operational and current, inclusive of ensuring that updates to key messaging or content for the platform’s Knowledge Base library are executed in a timely and effective manner • Maintaining user accounts to ensure account status, subscription type, pricing and promotions and other key attributes are accurate and up to date • Addressing user issues/questions as they arise, either through their own knowledge/direct actions or through timely consultation with other team members • Successfully executing digital outreach, inclusive of email campaigns and other communications through Mailchimp and social media accounts • Performing ad hoc research in support of the above activities, i.e. looking into a user’s website to better understand their product category in order to address an issue being experienced with their user profile on the platform, or helping identify key contact info for prospective brand and investor users of the platform, or potential operating/content partners • Performing ad hoc research of prospective users and managing contacts in the Brandjectory CRM • Providing final reviews of generated communications and content for the platform, inclusive of newsletters, emails and articles for use in either marketing or the Knowledge Base library, including tracking performance and feedback • Being an active participant in regular team meetings, inclusive of providing updates on key activities/initiatives and capturing key findings/takeaways from the group discussion In addition, the Platform Manager will possess strong communication (written and spoken) and interpersonal skills, allowing them to build effective relationships with the Brandjectory ‘ecosystem’ of users, partner and service providers (i.e. agencies). This role is anticipated to be a part-time position with an average weekly time commitment of 15-20 hours, although there may be variances week-to-week based on the specific needs of the business.
